  "theory": {
    "intro": "To order a mixed collection of fractions, decimals and percentages, put them all into the **same form** first. Converting each value to a decimal makes them easy to compare by place value; then rewrite the list in the original forms, in the new order.",
    "facts": [
      "Convert every value to a decimal so they can be compared directly.",
      "For decimals, compare place value from the left: $0.6>0.58$ because $6$ tenths beats $5$ tenths.",
      "For negatives, the value with the larger digits is the **smaller** number: $-0.75<-0.6$.",
      "Ascending means smallest to largest; descending means largest to smallest."
    ],
    "steps": [
      "Convert every value to a decimal.",
      "Order the decimals using place value, remembering that among negatives the larger the digits the smaller the number.",
      "Rewrite each value in its original form, keeping the new order."
    ]
  },
